            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Did you try `vim.fn.list2str`?\n\nStatus:\n\n- `vim.fn.list2str(list, utf8)` takes a list of codepoint integers and returns the concatenated UTF-8 string. This is functionally equivalent to Lua 5.3+'s `utf8.char(...)`:\n   ```\n   vim.fn.list2str({ 0x1F600, 0x1F914 }, true)  -- \"😀🤔\"\n   ```\n- `vim.fn.nr2char(n, utf8)` : single-codepoint variant. `nr2char(0xE220, true)` returns the UTF-8 bytes for U+E220.\n- `vim.str_utf_end` / `_pos` / `_start` / `_utfindex` / `_byteindex` are \"query\" interfaces; none construct strings from codepoints.\n\nNext steps:\n\n- If we still think this is necessary, would `vim.str_utf8()` make sense as the name?\n  - impl: wrap `utf_char2bytes`.\n",
